            <description>&lt;p&gt;
	Wilfried Porth, member of the board of management at Daimler AG, cautions against the assumption that the General Motors&amp;nbsp;bailout saved American jobs. He warns legislators against subsidizing the auto industry to the same extent as of the commercial airline industry.&lt;/p&gt;
